{"spanless":false,"short_desc":"measure a quantity of something","long_desc":"Useful to capture ingredients in recipes for instance, or quantities of food for health tracking apps.
Returns a numerical value, a unit, and a product (each field is optional).
If you use this entity, you MUST create two custom entities in your instance:
- unit: listing the units (cups, liters, grams...)
- product: listing the products (flour, wine, meat...)
wit/quantity will load these entities and use them to build quantities.","examples":[{"expression":["How many grams in","2 cups of flour","?"],"response":""entities" : {
      "quantity" : [ {
        "product" : "flour",
        "value" : 2,
        "unit" : "cup"
      } ]
    }","$$hashKey":"0XU"},{"expression":["How many cups in","two pounds","?"],"response":""entities" : {
      "quantity" : [ {
        "value" : 2,
        "unit" : "pound"
      } ]
    }","$$hashKey":"6PG"}],"similar_wisps":[{"name":"","$$hashKey":"0XW"}]}
